<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4914914>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 7. Palaeagapetus celsus male and female. Male (A–E): A, right wings, dorsal; B, abdominal segments V–X, left lateral; C, genitalia, left, lateral; D, same, dorsal; E, same, ventral. Female (F, G): F, abdominal segments V–X, left lateral; G, vaginal apparatus, ventral. Abbreviations: 1–5=1st to 5th apical forks; V–X=5th to 10th abdominal segments; tX=tergite X; ia=inferior appendage; la ap=lateral appendage: db=dorsal branch of lateral appendage, vb=ventral branch of lateral appendage, sp=slender process of lateral appendage; ph=phallus." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4914914/files/figure.png" .

